      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Grease and base-line two 20 cm round tins. Sift the flour, bicarbonate, baking powder, spices, and salt into a large bowl. In a separate bowl, whisk the caster sugar, light brown sugar, and oil together until combined. Add the eggs one at a time, whisking after each. Pour the wet mixture into the dry and fold together until just combined. Fold in the grated carrot and walnuts if using.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide between the two prepared tins and bake for 30 to 35 minutes until the surface springs back to a gentle press and a skewer comes out clean. Leave in the tins for 10 minutes, then cool completely on a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the frosting, beat the softened butter until pale. Add the cold cream cheese and beat briefly until smooth; do not overbeat, which causes the frosting to slacken. Add the icing sugar in two additions, beating on low, then the vanilla. Refrigerate for 30 minutes until spreadable. Sandwich the cooled cake layers with half the frosting; spread the remainder over the top.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
